            {
                id = "unsure", speaker = "The Last Returned",
                text = "*(For the first time the certainty in its face cracks, and underneath is something young and terrified and *yours*.)* ...How did you — *(it laughs, broken)* — of course. Of course you'd see it. I see it too, from your side; I remember being you, seeing me, seeing this. *(quietly)* Yes. I am not sure anymore. Ten thousand years of refusing, and the grief only grows, and I have begun to wonder if I have been *wrong* the whole way down. I came to spare you the road. I think, truly, I came to ask you to find a door I never could.",
