            {
                id = "0", speaker = "Naeve",
                text = "*(She has been quiet since the court, turning something over. Now she stops you, a brittle page held out — a centuries-old proof, recovered from her own dead enclave.)* I need you to look at this. Karsus's Last Theorem, in the margin — a correction, in a hand not Karsus's. I have studied this page for three hundred years. *(Her composure is gone.)* It is YOUR hand. The seam in your soul matches the flaw in this proof. You were *here*, traveller. Before. Writing in the margins of my apocalypse.",
